To achieve convergence and meet the SDG3 targets, several systemic challenges will need to be addressed. The main challenge for Mexico's health system is how to organise the finance and delivery systems around these interventions in a way that ensures effective access and high quality, and standardised performance across the country (panel 2
                     ). In addition, addressing mortality due to the leading risk factors (high body-mass index, high fasting plasma glucose, alcohol and tobacco use, and high blood pressure) and injuries will require strong collaboration between the health sector and other sectors, such as education, labour, fiscal, and more.
